# Topical Map

A bulleted list of questions you'd want to answer publicly, grouped by topic
pillar. The `topical_questions` scanner picks a few per day and surfaces them
in your morning Discord digest as `❓ answer` items — content prompts you can
turn into blog posts, LinkedIn articles, or videos.

The format is parsed by regex. Stick to it:

    ## Pillar — <pillar name>
    - <question 1>
    - <question 2>

Headings that don't match `## Pillar — ...` are ignored. Bullets under those
headings are ignored. So you can keep notes anywhere else in the file.

The same question won't re-surface within `TOPICAL_RECENT_DAYS` (default 21).
To force a re-emit, edit the question text — that changes its dedup slug.

---

## Pillar — Local LLMs

- How do you choose between Q3_K_M and Q4_K_M quantization for a 24GB GPU?
- When does a 7B local model beat a frontier API for your use case?
- What's the smallest model that can reliably produce strict JSON?
- How do you measure "good enough" for a local model replacing GPT-4o?

## Pillar — Personal AI infrastructure

- What does a "personal RAG" actually look like in practice?
- How do you ingest 10 years of personal email into a queryable index?
- What's the right database for an append-only log of agent activity?
- How do you keep an LLM from forgetting context across days?

## Pillar — Self-improving agents

- How does an agent edit its own prompts without going off the rails?
- What's the simplest feedback loop that actually improves agent performance?
- When does "self-refine" beat "more compute"?

## Pillar — Discord-as-UI

- Why is Discord a better agent UI than a custom web dashboard?
- What does the smallest useful Discord bot look like?
- How do you avoid notification fatigue from an always-on AI?

---

(Replace these pillars with YOUR own. The more specific the questions, the
better the content prompts.)
